<diary><title>Pineapple Cheesecake</title><category>recipe</category><date-time><date>26-12-2013</date><time>18:52:06</time></date-time><section><p>By Linda</p>
<p><strong><span style="background-color: #ff9900;">Ingrediants:</span></strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">8 plain wine biscuits</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">1/2 tsp cinnamon</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">1/2 tsp nutmeg</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">2 table spoons butter, melted</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">250g cream cheese</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">3 tsp sugar</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">juice of 1/2 lemon</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">200ml cream</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">few clrops vanilla essence</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">4 tsp cheaped gelatine</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">1/4 cup hot water</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">400gm tin unsweeted crushed pineapple</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="background-color: #ff9900;"><strong>Procedure</strong><strong>:</strong></span></p>
<ol>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">finely crush biscuits</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">add spices plus melted butter mixed well, press into 20cm round tin, chill</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">blend the cream cheese n sugar</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">add lemon juice and vanilla essence</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">dissolve gelatine in hot water</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">add pineapple mix to cream cheese mix</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">whip cream and carefully fold into mixture</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">spread into chilled crumb base chill.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="background-color: #ff0000;">NOTE:</span></p>
<p><span style="background-color: #ffffff;">Make sure cream is whipped and everything ready to mix together before you add the gelatine to pineapple as it sets very quickly.</span></p></section></diary>